name: Absentia's Acrocanthosaurus
description:
The Absentia Additions team brings to you the Acrocanthosaurus, a PvP based apex that relies on outlasting it's opponents in mitigation, debuffing, and bleed based attacks. 
﻿
Rise above your enemies in rhythmic based combat to block attacks with your Parry, paired with ravenous abilities to overpower your opponents to take claim of true Apex Predator. Being top of the food chain is no easy task, are you up to the challenge?
 
Featuring accurate and stylized subspecies, we have something for everyone.

name: Ancient Gods: Camarasaurus
description:
This mod introduces a stylized Camarasaurus with over 25 gameplay abilities and items with an emphasis on skillful building and counter building. It has two crit zones, the base of the tail for damage and the belly for bleed / venom.

Challengers beware, for this ancient god is no gentle giant.

--

Ancient Gods is a mod collection inspired but not constrained by science. All creatures for the Ancient Gods collection are gameplay oriented first, with everything else designed around that fact.

name: Cubensis
description:
The herbivorous Cubensis is a unique, cube-shaped organism with a fleshy body that moves efficiently across various terrains, even able to hover over steep cliffs. In terms of strategy, they are highly tactical, using "hit and run" and "wait-and-see" methods to outsmart stronger opponents. They can delay an attacker, creating a temporary wall of flesh to slow down the threat. Despite their love for moisture, they fear drowning and will remain energized as long as they struggle to swim, though if they calm, they will eventually sink.

name: Divine Beasts: Acrocanthosaurus
description:
Divine Beasts is a Sciencefiction based mod, we don't claim realism and will take creative liberties where we see fit both in gameplay and design!

Acrocanthosaurus was a bipedal predator. As the name suggests, it is best known for the high neural spines on many of its vertebrae, which most likely supported a ridge of muscle over the animal's neck, back, and hips.

theDoctorTHE11th/Leviathan/Oska/Gisli

name: Divine Ports: Dryosaurus
description:
Original model by Scorching_Kami

Dryosaurus was a genus of dryosaurid ornithopod dinosaur from the late Jurassic of western North America. It has been discovered in Colorado, Wyoming, and Utah within the Morrison formation

Maintained by the Divine Beasts team.

name: Divine Ports: Helicoprion
description:
Original model by Scorching_Kami

Helicoprion is an extinct genus of shark-like eugeneodont fish. Almost all fossil specimens are of spirally arranged clusters of the individuals' teeth, called "tooth whorls", which in life were embedded in the lower jaw. As with most extinct cartilaginous fish, the skeleton is mostly unknown.

Maintained by the Divine Beasts team.

name: Divine Ports: Inostrancevia
description:
Original model by Scorching_Kami

Inostrancevia is an extinct genus of carnivorous therapsids, containing the largest members of the family Gorgonopsidae, predators characterized by long, saber-tooth-like canines. The various species inhabited northern Russia and South Africa during the Upper Tatarian.

Maintained by the Divine Beasts team.

name: Divine Ports: Kryptops
description:
Original model by Scorching_Kami

Kryptops is a genus of theropod dinosaur from the Early Cretaceous of Niger. It is known from a partial skeleton found at the Gadoufaoua locality in the western Ténéré Desert, in rocks of the Aptian-Albian age Elrhaz Formation. The genus name means "covered face", in reference to evidence that the face bore a tightly-adhering covering.

Maintained by the Divine Beasts team.

name: Divine Ports: Mosasaurus
description:
Original model by Scorching_Kami

Mosasaurus is an extinct aquatic reptile that lived at the very end of the Cretaceous Period, from around 82.7 to 66 million years ago. Mosasaurus was not a dinosaur; like other mosasaurs, it was descended from lizards that originally lived on land. Because of this, Mosasaurus belongs to the reptilian order Squamata, which contains all lizards and snakes.

Maintained by the Divine Beasts team.

name: KTO Mysteries | Dryptosaurus
description:
Dryptosaurus is a 2 slot carnivore with multiple head and arms slots giving it diverse builds and allowing it to combo bleeding claw attacks with powerful bites without cooldowns.

Mod made by Sergi

name: KTO Mysteries | Nanuqsaurus
description:
Nanuqsaurus is a medium sized tyrannosaur. Armed with a powerful bite, it possesses high damage attacks and the ability to splinter bones. It is also capable of healing itself and cleansing itself of status effects by cleaning its wounds, making it an effective combatant against whatever opposes it.

Skins by Fluff and Sergi
Everything else by Sergi

name: KTO Mysteries | Yangchuanosaurus
description:
Yangchuanosaurus is a large predator with multiple bleed abilities that make it a powerful big game hunter. Its speed is low but it has a large stamina pool to travel long distances and chase down big prey. Yangchuanosaurus' turn radius makes it a formidable opponent, allowing it to reliably land attacks on you whilst standing its ground.

Skins by Fluff and Sergi
Everything else by Sergi

name: Maplewood
description:
Psycho Dodo Clan presents: Maplewood
A great 10x10 expanse of forest, grasslands, marsh/wetlands/sloughs, and lakes/rivers!
Look for information signs, learn about the park!
High altitude brings great fog!
Computer weather control =  o key
Time and weather control on console: R3
Mobile: Volume down
Night vision = computer - n
Console - L2

*PHOTOSENSATIVITY WARNING: THIS MAP HAS LIGHTNING!*

Special thanks to Fortress (FBTH) for helping me out with some aspects of the map!

name: Najuro
description:
A map focused for a Sandbox Setting / Chill / Deathmatch environment. Najuro brings in a jungle environment as well as open areas, Homecaves, water & elements / fun you, the players can have fun climbing.

By completing a quest you get 10.000 Marks automatically, and a fair bit of growth.

- The map has 3 points containing food. 

Have fun!

name: TGB: Japanese Giant Salamander
description:
The Japanese Giant Salamander could end up like the rest of the prehistoric creatures in this game, extinct. To help raise awarness of the species and it's plight I thought what better way to do so then adding it to Path of Titans.
Help support this animal by searching up sustainable daisen.
As big as the Japanese Giant Salamander is we have scaled up this prehistoric animal.
Mod Created by the Divine Beasts Team: theDoctorTHE11th/SadEch/Matheusfers/Gisli
Skins : Xseidet/FowlMarlee
Emote Art : Grana

name: The Crimson Isle's Cryolophosaurus
description:
The Crimson Isle’s Cryolophosaurus

Cryolophosaurus, known as the "frozen crested lizard", is a distinctive theropod that roamed the Earth around 190 million years ago. Discovered in the early 1990s in Antarctica, this dinosaur's in-game variant introduces new behaviors and interactions.

Created by: Feilong with the help of TheDoctorTHE11th, with contributions from Toa Metru and M-Z and VividSky.  

Special Thanks: GigaPark, Pi, the WOTG mod team and The Crimson Isle Mod Team.

name: Titanus Constructus: Ampelosaurus
description:
A mid-sized armored sauropod specializing in a defensive game style, Ampelosaurus is not an easy foe to contend with. Armed with decently sized spines, and sometimes osteoderms, this dinosaur is built for wear and tear.
Only the bravest apexes dare challenge an adult. A pair however may prove challenging for a lone Ampelosaurus.

name: Titanus Constructus: Citipati
description:
This mod adds the smaller mid-tier oviraptorid, Citipati to your game. Playable as a speedy solo, or a supportive group, there is no wrong way to enjoy this silly dinosaur!

“Beak Snap” and "Threaten" emote animation by DefinitelyNotDilo.

name: Zealandia Natural
description:
Discover an ultra-realistic skin mod, designed for total immersion in the world of Zealandia, a unique server that plunges you into the heart of a reserve populated by prehistoric animals. This mod is specially adapted for players who wish to live an authentic experience among these giants from another time.

A huge thank you to Smaug for his valuable contribution in making this project a reality.
And also to the entire Zealandia staff for their useful and precise help on fixing issues.
